Kiambu teachers through Knut, Kenya Primary School Head Teachers Association, vocational training colleges leaders, and Kuppet have resolved to support Ferdinand Waititu, better known as Baba Yao, for governor.Speaking yesterday in Ruaka, Kiambaa constituency, Kiambu West Knut secretary Michael Muna said teachers have agreed to work with Waititu&rsquo;s team so that he can improve education.&ldquo;The current government has never held a meeting with stakeholders in the education sector,&rdquo; he said.Muna spoke after meeting Baba Yao&rsquo;s team, who included his running mate James Nyoro, among others. Baba Yao wants to unseat Governor William Kabogo, an independent.